Sandy Duck SCHISM + DATM (ERA5) Coupled Run Template
=====================================================

Domain: Sandy Duck, North Carolina
Grid: 45,167 nodes, 23,018 elements, 31 vertical levels (hybrid S/Z)
Coupling: DATM (ERA5 0.25deg) + SCHISM via CMEPS mediator
Forecast: 6 hours (2012-10-27 00:00 - 06:00 UTC)
MPI Tasks: 320 (160 ATM + 160 OCN) on 4 nodes

Files included in template (config only):
  param.nml        - SCHISM ocean model namelist
  model_configure  - FV3/UFS atmosphere configuration
  ufs.configure    - NEMS/CMEPS coupling configuration
  datm_in          - Data atmosphere namelist
  datm.streams     - DATM stream config (ERA5 wind/pressure)
  vgrid.in         - Vertical grid (31-level hybrid S/Z)
  bctides.in       - Tidal boundary conditions
  station.in       - Output station locations (5 stations at Duck, NC)
  run_ufs.sh       - SLURM submission script

Files you must provide (domain-specific):
  hgrid.gr3        - Horizontal grid (Cartesian)
  hgrid.ll         - Horizontal grid (lat/lon)
  rough.gr3        - Bottom roughness
  diffmin.gr3      - Min horizontal diffusivity
  diffmax.gr3      - Max horizontal diffusivity
  windrot_geo2proj.gr3 - Wind rotation angles
  elev.ic          - Initial elevation condition
  wwmbnd.gr3       - Wave boundary definition
  elev2D.th.nc     - 2D elevation time history
  INPUT/era5_*.nc  - ERA5 atmospheric forcing data
  INPUT/mesh_datm.nc - DATM mesh file

Executables you must provide:
  ufs_model (or fv3_coastalS_V3.exe) - Compiled UFS-Coastal binary
  module-setup.sh  - Module loader for your platform
  modulefiles/     - Platform module files
